</title>
<subSubSection id="CB429C4DA9B5F3B26752A24C8CEA65D2" pageId="null" pageNumber="564" type="description">
<paragraph id="775AEB027B2041D7D28C57FDA473EF3C" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="119ECE90AE3BA9464DE4A464DCE7FAD7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Astragalus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="null" pageNumber="564" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="danicus">
<emphasis id="46D767CB19536929989B27F0300A3199" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">A. danicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 11) durch folgende Merkmale: 
<normalizedToken id="32E387F7B116BBC45897462A1667899A" originalValue="Teilblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Teilblaetter</normalizedToken>
ausgerandet; 
<normalizedToken id="E8B17F6A2A89B76BC748458F82843E37" originalValue="Nebenblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Nebenblaetter</normalizedToken>
bis zu etwa ⅓ verwachsen; 
<emphasis id="E6252F8B820E1EF48D495227292AE6C3" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">
<normalizedToken id="395BAA6783E4DDB93EC6ED1440F2F4C0" originalValue="Tragblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Tragblaetter</normalizedToken>
fast so lang wie die 
<normalizedToken id="9FDA0C40C7DFB74961E299994C4F32FF" originalValue="Kelchröhre" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Kelchroehre</normalizedToken>
;
</emphasis>
Kelch 0,8-1 cm lang; 
<normalizedToken id="93B9A59E4F5EC73D07BD6662D2CFF73F" originalValue="Kelchzähne" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Kelchzaehne</normalizedToken>
⅔ so lang wie die 
<normalizedToken id="0DCDFEE519A5C9ECC7CF48042758980B" originalValue="Kelchröhre" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Kelchroehre</normalizedToken>
; 
<emphasis id="BF5FB87D9026CADF5CB318057A8660F6" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Krone purpurn; Falme 1</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="A8FACCEFA16AC24A38A371E08180AF8C" originalValue="½" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">1/2</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="3F5444A7BE97DEF1272D95D2EADA1B73" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">
mal so lang wie die 
<normalizedToken id="C268FD2CB4C8B62578F5EF6DB4678CAC" originalValue="Flügel" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Fluegel</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
(bei allen andern Arten im Gebiet 
<normalizedToken id="063DBFF988BE57E44581DC2F3613EAEE" originalValue="außer" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">ausser</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="AFEF875B10925128066AD4AB5F12A178" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">
A. 
<taxonomicName id="D4FF79F00475FB002E6328F934118AEC" authority="Nr." authorityName="Nr." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Onobrychis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="null" pageNumber="564" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Onobrychis Nr.</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
9 
<normalizedToken id="FDF6D7AAA4A2110265FD17781639F902" originalValue="höchstens" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">hoechstens</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="C8DDCD7BE0146E20C71C231ABC1D7422" originalValue="1¼" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">11/4</normalizedToken>
mal so lang!); Frucht 1-1,5 cm lang und 0,4-0,5 cm dick. - 
<normalizedToken id="CB26E70E1CACFB05C77034CE0EF37F44" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: 
<normalizedToken id="DDFBA0265EB74D70817D41B24FA5249A" originalValue="Später" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Spaeter</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="B30D698E93313443B2F9E62700AD4FD4" originalValue="Frühling" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Fruehling</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="6B624FB52D11702F1686A3F312B70325" originalValue="früher" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">frueher</normalizedToken>
Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ECB853641B802539B6203807BB7C4446" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis id="DD746F1A5BDB257D72B8CA9A2F62370A" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="8243360B0FC911F544D192A62FBF3B69" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">16:</emphasis>
Material (als 
<taxonomicName id="33D2F3D00CD4721FA927E40900DD0CF9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cytisus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="null" pageNumber="564" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpureus">
<emphasis id="C654362F50494FC543A385C1E412D23A" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">A. purpureus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) aus Osteuropa (Ledingham und Rever 1963), von der Grigna im Comerseegebiet (Favarger 1969).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="07B3B4A29F52985302379C11A38BC243" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis id="6C999B7BE0878169F051688D16A0879C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin und montan, seltener subalpin. Trockene, steinige, kalkhaltige 
<normalizedToken id="1FBE5AC9696F72A47B11A04FC6CFCF5B" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Boeden</normalizedToken>
in warmen Lagen. Felsensteppen, Trockenwiesen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA293B588FA882C61D691ED306BA83DA" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis id="D641267D4ABD6ABD4ACE4A3FDDB40A91" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">
Verbreitung. 
<normalizedToken id="02E63F8198D0ED23F630942523CF7CE8" originalValue="Südeuropäische" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Suedeuropaeische</normalizedToken>
Gebirgspflanze
</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="D6F127D9A59F154A424F1FE20B6B3C19" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">
<normalizedToken id="A8CD098468A15CE3BFB3BE451EB3706A" originalValue="östlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">oestlich</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
)
<emphasis id="F911CD358C26BBD41BCF1C15689BFC57" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">:</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="923E3429F4C6E1CB4C1937A51A372C7F" originalValue="Südalpen" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Suedalpen</normalizedToken>
, Apennin (Toskana), Gebirge der Balkanhalbinsel (
<normalizedToken id="3B15E7D32D8A5DA60F29EF877E86F565" originalValue="südwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">suedwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Albanien). Verbreitungskarte von Meusel et al. (1965). - Im Gebiet: Aostatal (Brisogne, Monte Rosa), Grigna, Bergamasker Alpen (Carenno).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2C2FF3B2529542C2151BC3107817E04F" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis id="24B187FFD13AF0B63FCEAB4E1503E0E7" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Bemerkungen.</emphasis>
Die nahe verwandte 
<normalizedToken id="CD5F560D79C7FE2132BA4978FF412D5C" originalValue="südwesteuropäische" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">suedwesteuropaeische</normalizedToken>
Gebirgspflanze 
<taxonomicName id="14625186EC75EB8BD974862DB048DB21" authority="Lam." authorityName="Lam." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cytisus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="null" pageNumber="564" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" sensu="stricto" species="purpureus">
<emphasis id="4F7623DE603D2F7AA32322E3586B729B" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">A. purpureus</emphasis>
Lam.
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3D6A299E1F856135F072AD6F5B8DE44D" pageId="null" pageNumber="564" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
unterscheidet sich vor allem durch die 
<normalizedToken id="73196375DBE4C3EE98CABB811DF94A50" originalValue="längere" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">laengere</normalizedToken>
, zottige Stengelbehaarung. Sie tritt dem Gebiet am 
<normalizedToken id="5B415F23277F38387AD952739D81A938" originalValue="nächsten" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">naechsten</normalizedToken>
(z.T. in 
<normalizedToken id="B3F4BEA4F7A2A602C3BAE5E1FC4173A7" originalValue="Übergangsformen" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Uebergangsformen</normalizedToken>
zu 
<taxonomicName id="5F74AE4611A84589F73965CFB393EC25" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Astragalus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="null" pageNumber="564" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gremlii">
<emphasis id="71B94C7BA85DC9F6CB136B549F1DA11B" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">A. Gremlii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in der 
<normalizedToken id="9EFFC0993D5C548B9620B125710B26ED" originalValue="Dauphiné" pageId="null" pageNumber="564">Dauphine</normalizedToken>
auf.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
